<section class="hero" title="Hero Banner">
    <div>
        <h1>From static site to ecommerce platform in a matter of minutes.</h1>
        <p>All you need is your static site, a Stripe account, and Launch Cart.</p>
        <%= link "Get Started Now", to: Routes.user_registration_path(@conn, :new), class: "button button--cta" %>
    </div>
    <div class="hero__images">
        <div class="hero__image marketing-image"></div>
        <div class="hero__image marketing-image"></div>
        <div class="hero__image marketing-image"></div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="u-text-center" title="How-to Overview">
    <h2>It's as easy as 1-2-3</h2>
    <p>
        Including Launch Cart in your website really is as easy at it gets. All it takes is some simple setup and a single <code class="language-html">script</code> tag and you're able to use the custom elements!
        Not sure if Launch Cart fits your needs? Check out the demo site below.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/launchscout/demo-store" target="blank">See it in action</a>

    <div>
        <ol class="steps-list" title="The Steps">
            <li>
                <h3>Connect and create</h3>
                <p>Register for a Launch Cart account, connect your Stripe account, and create a Launch Cart store.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>Include in your website</h3>
                <p>We'll generate the script tag to copy + paste into your <code>head</code> block.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>Start using Launch Cart</h3>
                <p>Just copy + paste the Launch Cart custom HTML elements where you want them in your markup and voila! </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="contained-width" title="Customization">
    <div class="u-grid u-grid--stretch">
        <div class="detail-images detail-images--front-left">
            <div class="detail-images__image marketing-image">
                <%= img_tag(Routes.static_path(@conn, "/images/part-selectors.png"), alt: "Screenshot of custom CSS") %>
            </div>
            <div class="detail-images__image marketing-image">
                <%= img_tag(Routes.static_path(@conn, "/images/slot-code.png"), alt: "Screenshot of slot code") %>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>Fully Customizable or Ready to Use Out of the Box</h2>
            <p>
                Customization is entirely up to you! Because Launch Cart is custom HTML elements you can style them with CSS just like the rest of your site. So, you can use the default styles or roll your ownâ€”dealer's choice! 
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

